column2: Objective-C Twitter integration library for Mac OS X and iPhone. Official repository.

column5: message
Placated compiler re logging NS[U]Integer.
Added method to get information on a specific list with ID
Added method to update an existing list with the listID
Renamed method call from `createLists` to `createList`

Fixed issue where User node wasn't being created in the XML parser,
which caused the user id to take the place of the list id and the
results to not be properly structured.

Added method to create lists for authenticated users.
`- (NSString *)createListsForUser:(NSString *)username withName:(NSString *)listName withOptions:(NSDictionary *)options;`

Un depreciated setting the username in MGTwitterEngine.

This is to clean up the method definitions for Lists. A number of the calls require the user to the
authorised user (like list creation) which means it doesn't make sense to be able to specify a user.

This may change in the future should Twitter allow people to collaborate on lists.
Fixed warnings.

#39 Changes to MGTwitterEngine to provide fuller error messages.

* Lets clients check for rate-limiting headers and possibly provide more informative error messages to users.
* Pass back the response body when available
* Updated the README to describe the changes to the NSError passed into requestFailed:withError:

Merge branch 'master' of git://github.com/tarasis/MGTwitterEngine

Conflicts:
	MGTwitterEngine.m

Fixed error where I used ints and not "long long" values for the cursor's. Note I have not used MGTwitterEngineID as the cursors need to be signed, not unsigned.

I have also added some error checking in the getFollowerIDs & getFriendIDs; a cursor of 0 is invalid, as is a username name of "".

I have also changed the format of the request to match the other API request methods
Commented out a stray NSLog statment and added another.
Moved the Social Graph methods
Added a LibXML parser for the Social Graph API requests (friends/ids & followers/ids)
Merge commit 'matt/master'

Added initial support for the Social Graph API requests.

At present, I am only handling NSXML parsing. LibXML is next and YAJL once I have it built and installed on my system.

Forgot the 1/ from the API URL which indicates we are using version 1 of the Twitter API.

Without it some API calls will still work, others will fail. Hence I missed it during testing.
Updated MGTwitterEngine to use the new API domain http://api.twitter.com
Removed stray nslog.  Thanks to @alexrepty for pointing it out
